                                                       ()-()
  hidcur - Utility for hiding the mouse cursor in X11   \"/
=======================================================  `

Whenever the pointer is idle for more than the specified seconds, hidcur
creates an input window which grabs the pointer and sets an empty pixmap
cursor. Under any pointer activity, motion or button event, the window
is destroyed and the cursor recovers its original appearance.


 Usage
-------

hidcur <interval> | -h


 Dependencies
--------------

The XCB library and headers.


